<subSubSection lastPageId="124" lastPageNumber="125" pageId="123" pageNumber="124" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="124" lastPageNumber="125" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">
This species has been reported for Ladakh, India (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/2479452" author="Stewart, RR" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Torrey Botanical Club" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" pagination="625 - 650" refId="B98" refString="Stewart, RR, 1916. The flora of Ladak, Western Tibet. II. List of Ladak plants. Bulletin of the Torrey Botanical Club 43 (12): 625 - 650, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/2479452" title="The flora of Ladak, Western Tibet. II. List of Ladak plants." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/2479452" volume="43" year="1916">Stewart 1916</bibRefCitation>
). No specimens were seen from our territory and the nearest records are from Quetta, Pakistan (
<bibRefCitation author="Hedge, IC" editor="Rechinger, KH" journalOrPublisher="Akademische Druck- und Verlagsanstalt, Graz, 87 - 91" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" pagination="330 - 336" refId="B37" refString="Hedge, IC, 1997. Krascheninnikovia, Halocharis. In: Rechinger, KH, Ed., Flora Iranica 172. Akademische Druck- und Verlagsanstalt, Graz, 87-91: 330 - 336" title="Krascheninnikovia, Halocharis." volumeTitle="Flora Iranica 172." year="1997">Hedge 1997</bibRefCitation>
). This plant can be confused with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. A. Mey. in Ledeb., Fl. Altaic. 1: 378" authorityYear="1829" baseAuthorityName="M. Bieb." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chenopodiacea" genus="Halogeton" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Halogeton glomeratus" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="123" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glomeratus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="123" pageNumber="124">Halogeton glomeratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(re-identifications in BSD) and both species are woolly at younger stages. Both genera can be 
<pageBreakToken pageId="124" pageNumber="125" start="start">easily</pageBreakToken>
distinguished by the following leaf characteristics: the leaves of all 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chenopodiacea" genus="Halocharis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Halocharis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="124" pageNumber="125" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Halocharis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(tribe Caroxyleae) are covered with both short and long simple hairs, while those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. A. Mey. in Ledeb., Icon. Pl. 1: 10" authorityYear="1829" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chenopodiacea" genus="Halogeton" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Halogeton" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="124" pageNumber="125" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Halogeton</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(tribe Salsoleae) are glabrous or covered with short papillae (long, clearly visible hairs are present only at the leaf base). The presence of two hair types is a distinct characteristic of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chenopodiacea" genus="Halocharis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Halocharis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="124" pageNumber="125" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="124" pageNumber="125">Halocharis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
compared with many other 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Chenopodiaceae" genus="Salsoloideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="124" pageNumber="125" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">Salsoloideae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sukhorukov, AP" editor="Ghazanfar, SA" journalOrPublisher="5 (1). Bell and Bain Ltd, Glasgow" pageId="131" pageNumber="132" pagination="164 - 256" refId="B117" refString="Sukhorukov, AP, Aellen, P, Edmondson, JR, Townsend, CC, 2016b. Chenopodiaceae. In: Ghazanfar, SA, Edmondson, JR, Eds., Flora of Iraq, Vol. 5(1). Bell and Bain Ltd, Glasgow: 164 - 256" title="Chenopodiaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of Iraq, Vol." year="2016 b">Sukhorukov et al. 2016b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
